      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tapering down, even slowly, still requires professional medical oversight because warfarin's effect is not linear. You cannot accurately gauge the appropriate step-down dosage by just noticing how you \"feel.\" Your internal coagulation levels need to be tested with an INR check to ensure you aren't creeping into a dangerous clotting zone. Please call your doctor's office again and emphasize the urgency of getting that INR test done.",
